Author: TonyL#3577
Content: Minor/edge thing - AtomicDEX not handling "history too large" Electrum response (after AtomicDEX receiving it - RICK and MORTY dissappear from list without possibility to add it back until app restart

Author: TonyL#3577
Content:
As I understand electrum dont like low amount sums (or this error means that app started to "DDoS" electrum):
``` Started...03 05:40:26, utxo:1402] Electrum servers ["electrum2.cipig.net:10017", "electrum3.cipig.net:10017", "electrum1.cipig.net:10017"] ping error "jsonrpc_client:66] Rpc request JsonRpcRequest { jsonrpc: \"2.0\", id: \"25\", method: \"server.ping\", params: [] } failed with error, response: JsonRpcResponse { jsonrpc: \"2.0\", id: \"25\", result: Null, error: Object({\"code\": Number(-101), \"message\": String(\"excessive resource usage\")}) ```

3) thanks - we will add exception handler for "history too large" response
